# .dg-supervisor.env — per-machine config consumed by the supervisor at startup.
# Parsed by research.py's `_load_env_file()`.
#
# Format: KEY=value per line. `#` comments and blank lines OK. Outer matching
# quotes stripped. Whitespace around `=` forgiven. Malformed lines logged WARN
# and skipped (not fatal).
#
# Save as UTF-8 (no BOM). After editing, restart the supervisor:
#   Windows: schtasks /Run /TN SuperResearchBackend
#   macOS:   launchctl kickstart -k gui/$(id -u)/com.dgresearch.supervisor
#   Linux:   systemctl --user restart dgresearch-supervisor

# === Anthropic API key (used by both Vision and CUA tiers) ===
#
# Three source-of-truth options — DON'T set in multiple places with different
# values. resolve_api_key() priority chain wins as follows:
#   1. CLI --api-key flag (one-shot)
#   2. Firestore (FE Account page) — works on ALL platforms
#   3. Windows user-scope env (PowerShell SetEnvironmentVariable 'User')
#   4. os.environ (this .env file loads here via setdefault, plus shell rc)
#
# Recommended path: (a) FE "Account → API Config" — works on Windows,
# macOS, and Linux. Writes to users/{uid}/settings/prefs.apiKeys.anthropic
# in Firestore. Backend reads it via _read_firestore_api_keys() at use-time
# (60s cache, 5s on cache-miss). With the two-ladder fix from PR #2,
# vision.py and the CUA setup also route through resolve_api_key — so
# the FE-managed key wins everywhere on every platform.
#
# Alternative (b): uncomment ANTHROPIC_API_KEY below. Populates os.environ
# via setdefault. Useful for un-paired backends (no Firestore connection)
# or operators who prefer file-based config. Firestore still wins if both
# are set.
#
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# === Vision config ===
# Vision tier: off | shadow | tier2 | tier3
# DG_VISION_TIER=shadow

# Auto-harvest screenshots into tests/fixtures/vision/auto/<hotspot>/
# DG_VISION_FIXTURE_AUTO=1

# Override shadow-eval JSONL log path (default: logs/vision_shadow.jsonl)
# DG_VISION_SHADOW_LOG=

# Tag for Vision shadow records (change per Track A retest)
# DG_RUN_ID=track-a-2026-XX-XX

# === CUA config (rarely overridden) ===
# CUA_MODEL=claude-opus-4-7
# CUA_SCREEN_WIDTH=1280
# CUA_SCREEN_HEIGHT=800
